## Q1: インドから日本へ働きに来ようと決めた理由は？

### Question (English)
Why did you decide to come to Japan from India to work?  

### Question (Romaji)
Indo kara Nihon e hataraki ni koyou to kimeta riyuu wa?  

### Answer (English)
I have always been interested in Japan’s technology and manufacturing systems.  
I was fascinated by Japan’s precision and discipline in monozukuri.  
Through my studies at Shizuoka University, this passion grew stronger, and I decided to build my career in Japan.  
Working in Japan was one of my dreams, and I am truly grateful to this company for giving me the opportunity to learn, grow, and contribute, especially in fields where I can make a real impact.  

### Answer (Romaji)
Watashi wa tsune ni Nihon no gijutsu to seizō shisutemu ni kyomi motteimashita.  
Nihon no "monozukuri" ni okeru seimitsu sa to kiritsu ni miryō saremashita.  
Shizuoka Daigaku de no manabi o tsūjite kono jōnetsu wa sara ni tsuyomari Nihon de kyaria o kizuku koto o ketsui shimashita.  
Nihon de hataraku koto wa watashi no yume no hitotsu de ari, toku ni IoT ya robotikusu to itta bun'ya de jissai ni eikyō o ataerareru kankyō de manabi, seichō shi, kōken suru kikai o ataete kudasatta kono kaisha ni kokoro kara kansha shiteimasu.

---

## Q2: ここではどのような業務に携わっていますか？

### Question (English)
What kind of work are you doing here?  

### Question (Romaji)
Koko de wa dono you na gyoumu ni tazusawatte imasu ka?  

### Answer (English)
I work in the CPS Seigibu, focusing on research and development in IoT and AI robotics technology.  
My main work involves developing smart systems that improve automation and efficiency in projects.  
It’s very fulfilling because I get to combine AI and robotics to solve real-world problems.  

### Answer (Romaji)
CPS seigibu ni oite, IoT to AI robotikusu gijutsu no kenkyū kaihatsu ni chūryoku shiteimasu.  
Purojekuto no jidōka to kōritsuka o kōjō saseru sumāto shisutemu no kaihatsu ga omona gyōmu desu.  
AI to robotikusu o yūgō sasete genjitsu no kadai o kaiketsu dekiru ten ga hijō ni yarigai o kanjimasu.

---

## Q3: 仕事からどのような充実感を得ていますか？

### Question (English)
What kind of fulfillment do you feel from your work?  

### Question (Romaji)
Shigoto kara dono you na jūjitsukan o ete imasu ka?  

### Answer (English)
The most fulfilling part is seeing the ideas we develop actually applied in real systems.  
When a project succeeds or a problem is solved, I feel a strong sense of achievement.  
I also enjoy learning new technologies that constantly challenge me and keep me motivated.  

### Answer (Romaji)
Kaihatsu shita aidea ga jissai no shisutemu ni tekiyō sareru sugata o mirareru koto ga, mottomo yarigai o kanjimasu.  
Purojekuto ga seikō shitari mondai o kaiketsu shitari shita toki wa, ōkina tasseikan o eraremasu.  
Mata, tsune ni chōsen shi tsudzukerareru atarashii gijutsu o manabu koto mo tanoshimi de ari, mōtibēshon no minamoto desu.

---

## Q4: 今後どのような仕事に携わりたいですか？

### Question (English)
What kind of work would you like to be involved in going forward?  

### Question (Romaji)
Kongo dono you na shigoto ni tazusawaritai desu ka?  

### Answer (English)
As Japan’s technology is rapidly evolving, I would like to be part of this growth.  
I feel fortunate to work in a company that encourages innovation and supports learning.  
I hope to contribute to exciting projects, keep learning new technologies, and work on solutions that truly make a difference.  

### Answer (Romaji)
Nihon no gijutsu ga kyūsoku ni shinka suru naka, kono seichō no ichiyoku o nina itai to kangaete imasu.  
Kakushin o shōrei shi manabi o shien suru kono shokuba de hatarakeru koto o kōun ni kanjite imasu.  
Shigeki-teki na purojekuto ni kōken shi, arata na gijutsu o manabi tsudzuke, shin ni henka o motarasu sorūshon ni torikumitai to omoimasu.
